snippet.textDisplay:
I wanna put my input on dance rankings here since a lot of people like to argue with it. I’m saying this as a long time Kpop fan (since 2011 👉👈) and based of my own dance skills (I’ve been dancing since I was 6)
R A N K I N G S :
1st- Chaeryeong. The way she embodies the dance is spectacular. Her facial expressions, movements, and attention to details are amazing. She really shows her talents while dancing.
2nd- Yeji. I totally agree she is a CLOSE second to Chaeryeong. I think the only problem she has when dancing is she focuses too much on specific moments, which makes some moves sharp and clean and others still sharp and a little lazy looking. She gives her all while dancing to the hardest parts and she has great breath control! But she sadly has trouble with facial expressions sometimes.
3rd- Ryujin. OMFG SHES AMAZING! Compared to Chaeryeong and Yeji I think she could still be a main dancer, but of course she already had the center position. The way she moves makes the dance look effortless to her, she doesn’t look lazy and while her moves aren’t as sharp as say Yeji and Chaeryeong, she has her own style. A chic, swag, style. Her dancing reminds a lot of BLACKPINK Lisa!
Yuna: Yuna is AMAZING on stage. I think the only problem with her dancing is her attention to detail. She, like Yeji, focuses on main parts while on other pets looks a little bored. But when she’s on stage, looking bored or not, SHINES! She knows how to captivate the crowd.
Lia: I think Lia has improved IMMENSELY! She has a problem with her movements though. Like Ryujin I think dancing for her comes easy. While it’s not “main dancer” material, she definitely has the potential to be main dancer if she continues to improve. BUT- her problem is movement. While she has the kinda same movements as Ryujin, hers come off more “lazily” and she also doesn’t have good facial expressions while on others parts. BUT she still shines with her voice! People need to stop sleeping on Lia, and calling her lazy as her dance style is just like Ryujin! (Not as sharp though)
MIDZY FOREVER!! 🥰🥰
